approve(address,uint256).details: See {IERC20-approve}. NOTE: If `value` is the maximum `uint256`, the allowance is not updated on `transferFrom`. This is semantically equivalent to an infinite approval. Requirements: - `spender` cannot be the zero address.

params.lowerSqrtPriceLimitX96: The lower price limit of the pool.
params.shares: The amount of Burve LP token to burn.
params.upperSqrtPriceLimitX96: The upper price limit of the pool.

params._island: The optional island we are wrapping
params._weights: n weights defining the relative liquidity for each range.

decimals().details: Returns the number of decimals used to get its user representation. For example, if `decimals` equals `2`, a balance of `505` tokens should be displayed to a user as `5.05` (`505 / 10 ** 2`). Tokens usually opt for a value of 18, imitating the relationship between Ether and Wei. This is the default value returned by this function, unless it's overridden. NOTE: This information is only used for _display_ purposes: it in no way affects any of the arithmetic of the contract, including {IERC20-balanceOf} and {IERC20-transfer}.

params.newStationProxy: The new station proxy to migrate to.

params.lowerSqrtPriceLimitX96: The lower price limit of the pool.
params.mintNominalLiq: The amount of nominal liquidity to mint.
params.recipient: The recipient of the minted liquidity.
params.upperSqrtPriceLimitX96: The upper price limit of the pool.

name().details: Returns the name of the token.

queryTVL().details: As of now, this method is only used by off-chain queries where the minor errors are negligible. Do not use this where high-precision is required.

queryValue(address).details: As of now, this method is only used by off-chain queries where the minor errors are negligible. Do not use this where high-precision is required.

queryValueIsland(uint256).details: As of now, this method is only used by off-chain queries where the minor errors are negligible. Do not use this where high-precision is required.

queryValueV3Ranges(uint256).details: As of now, this method is only used by off-chain queries where the minor errors are negligible. Do not use this where high-precision is required.

params.shares: The amount of Burve LP token.

symbol().details: Returns the symbol of the token, usually a shorter version of the name.

transfer(address,uint256).details: See {IERC20-transfer}. Requirements: - `to` cannot be the zero address. - the caller must have a balance of at least `value`.

transferFrom(address,address,uint256).details: See {IERC20-transferFrom}. Skips emitting an {Approval} event indicating an allowance update. This is not required by the ERC. See {xref-ERC20-_approve-address-address-uint256-bool-}[_approve]. NOTE: Does not update the allowance if the current allowance is the maximum `uint256`. Requirements: - `from` and `to` cannot be the zero address. - `from` must have a balance of at least `value`. - the caller must have allowance for ``from``'s tokens of at least `value`.

distX96(uint256).notice: The relative liquidity for our n ranges. If there is an island that distribution lies at index 0.

islandSharesPerOwner(address).notice: Mapping of owner to island shares they own.

migrateStationProxy(address).notice: Allows the owner to migrate to a new station proxy.

queryTVL().notice: Queries the token amounts held by the contract. Ignoring leftover amounts.

queryValue(address).notice: Queries the token amounts in a user's position.

queryValueIsland(uint256).notice: Queries amounts in the island by simulating a burn.

queryValueV3Ranges(uint256).notice: Queries amounts in the v3 ranges by simulating burns.

ranges(uint256).notice: The n ranges. If there is an island that range lies at index 0, encoded as (0, 0).
